    icon: "📶",
    content: `**1. Bubble Sort:**
Repeatedly compares adjacent elements and swaps if in wrong order. Pass-through repeated until sorted.

**2. Selection Sort:**
Divides list into sorted and unsorted parts. Repeatedly selects the smallest element from unsorted part and swaps it with the first unsorted element.

**3. Insertion Sort:**
Builds the sorted array one item at a time. Takes each element and inserts it into the correct position in the sorted part.

**4. Merge Sort:**
Divide-and-conquer algorithm. Divides list into smaller sub-lists, sorts each, then merges them back into a single sorted list.

**5. Quick Sort:**
Picks a "pivot" element and partitions others into two sub-lists (less than pivot, greater than pivot). Recursively sorts both sub-lists.

**6. Heap Sort:**
Comparison-based algorithm that builds a binary heap from the list and repeatedly extracts the min/max element until sorted.`,
